The '''spotted thrush-babbler''' ('''''Illadopsis turdina''''') also known as the '''thrush babbler''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Pellorneidae]]. It is found in [[Angola]], [[Cameroon]], [[Central African Republic]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[South Sudan]], and [[Zambia]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and [[subtropical or tropical moist shrubland]].

